		<div id="comment_body_64266088"><p>The entire US national debate about Covid, whether vaccines are supposedly useless and dangerous, whether basic common sense measures to spread infectious disease are an assault on the constitutional rights of US citizens, etc, etc, ad nauseam,<nobr> <wbr></nobr>... that has dominated US public discourse and news cycles for years can now be summed up like this:</p><p>
&nbsp; - Florida has a population of 21,78 million people they are now counting 94,037 Covid deaths.</p><p>
&nbsp; - Japan has a population of 125,7 million people they are now counting 74,694 Covid deaths. </p><p>If Florida's government had displayed the same level of basic common sense and competence when dealing with the Covid pandemic as Japan's government did then Florida's Covid death toll would be just under 13,000 and this is just one US state we're talking about here that has a higher death toll than a country six times it's size. These numbers say all that needs to be said.</p></div>
	</div>

